member.summary: Provides methods to license the component.

member.name: M:Aspose.Finance.License.#ctor
member.summary: Initializes a new instance of this class.

member.name: M:Aspose.Finance.License.SetLicense(System.String)
member.summary: Licenses the component.

remarks.p: Tries to find the license in the following locations:

ms.p: 2. The folder that contains the Aspose component assembly.
3. The folder that contains the client's calling assembly.
4. The folder that contains the entry (startup) assembly.
5. An embedded resource in the client's calling assembly.
Note:On the .NET Compact Framework, tries to find the license only in these locations:
2. An embedded resource in the client's calling assembly.

java.p: 2. The current working directory of the java application.
3. The folder that contains the Aspose component JAR file.
4. The folder that contains the client's calling JAR file.

member.example:
In this example, an attempt will be made to find a license file named MyLicense.lic in the folder that contains
the component, in the folder that contains the calling assembly, in the folder of the entry assembly and then in the embedded resources of the calling assembly.
[C#]
License license = new License(); license.SetLicense("MyLicense.lic");
[Visual Basic]
Dim license As License = New License license.SetLicense("MyLicense.lic")
the component jar file:
License license = new License(); license.setLicense("MyLicense.lic"); Can be a full or short file name or name of an embedded resource. Use an empty string to switch to evaluation mode.

member.name: M:Aspose.Finance.License.SetLicense(System.IO.Stream)
member.summary: Licenses the component.
member.param: A stream that contains the license.

remarks.p: Use this method to load a license from a stream.

member.summary: Bill payment status code enum.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.PAIDOUTOFBAND
member.summary: A Payment has been initiated for this bill via a mechanism that does not report status via OFX. This status is intended to indicate the customer has paid the biller directly with cash or a check or has initiated an electronic payment through a mechanism that does not report payment status through OFX.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.AUTOPAY
member.summary: The Biller or Service Provider will initiate the payment based on a pre-authorization by the customer, typically a “good until cancelled” instruction with no defined end date. In the US this is often implemented using a recurring pre-authorized ACH debit, though some Billers offer preauthorized automatic payment through credit card.Examples include monthly deductions to cover a mortgage, regular payments from a checking account to a credit card, and the Automatic Payment Service (APS) offered by many utilities.Like NONE, this may be the initial payment status of the bill.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.CANCELLED
member.summary: The customer cancelled the payment that was previously scheduled.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.UNPAYABLE
member.summary: None of the Payment Instruments allowed for this bill are supported by the Payment Provider. This is intended to be used where the bill restricts payment to a subset of the Payment Instruments allowed in the Biller Directory entry. This could occur if the Payment Provider or the Biller changed their supported payment instrument types after enrollment and account activation.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.NONE
member.summary: There is neither a payment scheduled, nor has one been made against this bill. This may be the initial payment status of a bill.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.SCHEDULED
member.summary: A payment has been scheduled, but not yet processed against this bill.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.PROCESSED
member.summary: The payment has been processed against this bill, and can no longer be cancelled.

member.name: F:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.BillerDelivery.BillPaymentStatusCodeEnum.POSTED
member.summary: The biller has posted the payment against this bill.

member.name: T:Aspose.Finance.Ofx.SecurityId
member.summary: Securities must be consistently identified to allow client applications to prepare accurate investment reports across all user investment accounts, even at multiple FIs.At this time, neither a security name nor its symbol is standardized.Therefore, OFX uses CUSIP numbers (a unique 9-digit alphanumeric identifier) to identify securities. CUSIP numbers are available for the vast majority of securities traded today, including those without symbols such as bonds. For a security that does not have a CUSIP, a financial institution must follow the standard procedure of assigning a CUSIP by using itself as the issuer to avoid conflict with any other CUSIP.

member.name: T:Aspose.Finance.Xbrl.Tuple
member.summary: A tuple is an element in the substitution group for the XBRL tuple element. Tuples are used to bind together the parts of a compound fact. Those constituent parts are themselves, facts but they must be interpreted in light of each-other. For example, the name, age and compensation of a director of a company need to be grouped together to be correctly understood.
